@startuml recall-internal-search
' SEQUENCE: the Recall brute-force search INTERNALS in isolation
' (adapters.state.state.recall_search). TWO separate, load-bearing scans over
' the SAME (tenant, dataset) partition, both filtered lsn > :watermark:
'   (a) MATCH scan   -- NOT deleted, ORDER BY embedding <-> q,
'                       score = power(<->, 2) = L2^2 (FAISS-aligned)
'   (b) SUPPRESS scan -- every id above the watermark (live AND tombstoned)
' Then a Python pass: take top_k live filter-passing rows as matches; the full
' id set is the suppress set. The cross-tier merge itself is NOT shown here
' (that is the tandem query-union diagram) -- this is Recall's own scan.

title Recall internals: brute-force exact search (two scans)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowFontSize 11
skinparam NoteFontSize 10
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

participant "caller\n(recall_search)" as rs
database "recall_vectors\n(one (tenant,dataset)\npartition)" as rv

note over rs #E7F3FD
  Why EXACT full-partition scan is fine:
  the recall set is bounded by CONSOLIDATION
  CADENCE, not data size (cap + idle drain) --
  hundreds-to-thousands of rows -> sub-ms,
  ZERO recall loss, no ANN index churn.
end note

== (a) MATCH scan -- live rows, ranked ==

rs -> rv : SELECT id, power(embedding <-> q, 2) AS score, metadata\nWHERE tenant_id=? AND dataset=? AND NOT deleted AND lsn > :watermark\nORDER BY embedding <-> q ASC
activate rv
note right of rv #E9F7E9
  score = power(<->, 2) = L2^2 so it merges
  DIRECTLY with FAISS L2^2 (metric alignment;
  both tiers store the SAME un-normalised vecs).
  NOT deleted keeps tombstones out of the
  ranking in SQL (a zero-vector tombstone can
  never sort first / crowd out a real match).
end note
rv --> rs : ranked live rows
deactivate rv

== (b) SUPPRESS-id scan -- every id above the watermark ==

rs -> rv : SELECT id\nWHERE tenant_id=? AND dataset=? AND lsn > :watermark\n(live AND tombstoned; no filter, no top_k)
activate rv
rv --> rs : full id set above the watermark
deactivate rv

== Python post-pass ==

rs -> rs : matches = first top_k LIVE rows\nthat pass the AND-of-equals filter\n(tombstones never match)
rs -> rs : suppress_ids = EVERY id above the watermark
note over rs #FDF3E7
  Returns (suppress_ids, matches).
  Recall is authoritative for lsn > watermark, so
  suppress_ids drops the stale cold twin of ANY such
  id -- tombstoned, filtered-out, or past top_k.
end note

@enduml
